on%20to%20Bills%20passed%20by%20state%20legislatures.%20The%20Court%20ruled%20that%20the%20Governor%20cannot%20indefinitely%20delay%20or%20withhold%20assent%20to%20a%20Bill%2C%20emphasising%20that%20such%20actions%20undermine%20the%20legislative%20process%20and%20the%20supremacy%20of%20the%20elected%20representatives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20verdict%20released%20on%20November%2010%20and%20made%20public%20last%20evening%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20delivered%20a%20judgment%20on%20a%20petition%20filed%20by%20the%20AAP%20government%20in%20Punjab%2C%20which%20contended%20that%20Governor%20Banwarilal%20Purohit%20was%20withholding%20his%20approval%20of%20four%20Bills%20passed%20by%20the%20state%20assembly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Governor%20cannot%20be%20at%20liberty%20to%20keep%20the%20Bill%20pending%20indefinitely%20without%20taking%20any%20action%20whatsoever.%20Failing%20to%20make%20a%20decision%20and%20keeping%20a%20duly%20passed%20Bill%20pending%20for%20indeterminate%20periods%20is%20a%20course%20of%20action%20inconsistent%20with%20that%20expression%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20bench%20comprising%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20DY%20Chandrachud%2C%20Justice%20JB%20Pardiwala%20and%20Justice%20Manoj%20Misra%2C%20in%20a%2027-page%20judgment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Governor%2C%20as%20an%20unelected%20Head%20of%20State%2C%20is%20entrusted%20with%20certain%20constitutional%20powers.%20However%2C%20these%20powers%20cannot%20be%20used%20to%20thwart%20the%20normal%20course%20of%20lawmaking%20by%20the%20state%20legislatures%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bench%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Punjab%20government%20has%20also%20requested%20a%20formal%20judicial%20declaration%20that%20the%20assembly%20session%20held%20on%20June%2019%20and%2020%20was%20legally%20conducted%20and%20that%20all%20actions%20taken%20by%20the%20House%20during%20that%20session%20were%20valid.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20a%20parliamentary%20form%20of%20democracy%2C%20the%20true%20power%20lies%20with%20the%20elected%20representatives%20of%20the%20people.%20The%20Governor%2C%20an%20appointee%20of%20the%20President%2C%20serves%20as%20the%20titular%20head%20of%20state%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20bench%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fundamental%20principle%20of%20constitutional%20law%2C%20consistently%20followed%20since%20the%20Constitution's%20adoption%2C%20is%20that%20the%20Governor%20acts%20on%20the%20'aid%20and%20advice'%20of%20the%20council%20of%20ministers%2C%20except%20in%20those%20areas%20where%20the%20Constitution%20has%20entrusted%20the%20Governor%20with%20the%20exercise%20of%20discretionary%20power%2C%20the%20Court%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20principle%20cements%20the%20bedrock%20of%20the%20constitutional%20foundation%20that%20the%20power%20to%20make%20decisions%20affecting%20the%20governance%20of%20the%20state%2C%20or%20the%20nation%20as%20a%20whole%2C%20rests%20fundamentally%20with%20the%20elected%20branch%20of%20government%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20judgment%20stated.%20%26quot%3BThe%20Governor%20is%20intended%20to%20be%20a%20constitutional%20statesman%2C%20guiding%20the%20government%20on%20matters%20of%20constitutional%20concern.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20running%20feud%20has%20marred%20ties%20between%20Governor%20Purohit%20and%20the%20AAP%20government%20in%20Punjab%2C%20helmed%20by%20Chief%20Minister%20Bhagwant%20Mann.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGovernor%20Purohit%20on%20November%201%20approved%20two%20of%20the%20three%20bills%20presented%20to%20him%2C%20reversing%20his%20earlier%20stance%20of%20subjecting%20all%20proposed%20laws%20to%20a%20rigorous%20review%20before%20allowing%20them%20to%20be%20introduced%20in%20the%20assembly.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20bills%20were%20enacted%20during%20the%20June%2019-20%20session%20of%20the%20Punjab%20Assembly%2C%20which%20Governor%20Purohit%20had%20previously%20deemed%20%26quot%3Bpatently%20illegal.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20week%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20heard%20a%20similar%20plea%20by%20the%20Tamil%20Nadu%20government%20over%20the%20delays%20in%20clearing%20bills%20in%20the%20southern%20state.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700796960000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2020-07%2Fasu3jbbc_tamil-nadu-governor-banwarilal-purohit-650_625x300_29_July_20.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fcant-keep-bill-pending-indefinitely-supreme-court-raps-punjab-governor-4601498%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Supreme%20Court%20ruled%20that%20the%20Governor%20cannot%20indefinitely%20delay%20or%20withhold%20assent%20to%20a%20Bill%2C%20emphasising%20that%20such%20actions%20undermine%20the%20legislative%20process%20and%20the%20supremacy%20of%20the%20elected%20representatives.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fcant-keep-bill-pending-indefinitely-supreme-court-raps-punjab-governor-4601498%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fcant-keep-bill-pending-indefinitely-supreme-court-raps-punjab-governor-4601498%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fcant-keep-bill-pending-indefinitely-supreme-court-raps-punjab-governor-4601498%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'He's%20almost%20positive...'%3A%20Rohit's%20daughter%20offers%20adorable%20insights%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700796924000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-105460884%2Cimgsize-47768.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fsports%2Fcricket%2Fnews%2Fhe-is-almost-positive-rohit-sharmas-daughter-offers-adorable-insights-into-india-skippers-post-world-cup-phase%2Farticleshow%2F105460735.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India's%20skipper%20Rohit%20Sharma%20admitted%20to%20the%20media%20after%20In