fbb8d4ca513d8242e1a4d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221362%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EDavid%20Ryder%20%2F%20Stringer%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ECFTC%20says%20case%20against%C2%A0Changpeng%20Zhao%20and%20Binance%20is%20the%20beginning%20of%20an%20aggressive%20pursuit.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECommissioner%20Caroline%20D.%20Pham%20said%20the%20CFTC%20has%20no%20borders%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20prosecuting%20non-US%20entities.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBinance%20and%20Zhao%20to%20pay%20%244.3%20billion%20in%20fines.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20couple%20of%20years%20have%20been%20tough%20for%20the%20crypto%20industry%20and%20its%20leading%20figures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20it's%20not%20likely%20there%20will%20be%20relief%20for%20the%20sector%20anytime%20soon.%20At%20least%2C%20that's%20what%20policymakers%20are%20signaling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20week%2C%20Binance%20chief%20Changpeng%20Zhao%20joined%20his%20former%20industry%20rival%20Sam%20Bankman-Fried%20in%20making%20headlines%20for%20charges%20against%20him%20and%20his%20crypto%20exchange%2C%20which%20included%20breaching%20US%20anti-money-laundering%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Tuesday%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fcurrencies%2Fbinance-ceo-cz-guilty-plea-department-of-justice-money-laundering-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EZhao%20pleaded%20guilty%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20left%20his%20role%20as%20CEO.%20Binance%20is%20set%20to%20pay%20over%20%244.3%20billion%20in%20fines%2C%20%2450%20million%20of%20which%20will%20be%20paid%20by%20the%20former%20CEO%20himself.%20A%20portion%20of%20that%20will%20go%20to%20settle%20claims%20made%20by%20the%20Commodity%20Futures%20Trading%20Commission%20for%20allowing%20US%20customers%20to%20trade%20unregistered%20crypto%20derivatives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20statement%20made%20by%20CFTC%20Commissioner%20Christy%20Goldsmith%20Romero%20read%3A%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20no%20pirate%20ships%20in%20US%20markets%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20%26quot%3Baccess%20to%20US%20customers%20is%20a%20privilege%2C%20not%20a%20right.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoldsmith%20added%20that%20the%20CFTC%20plans%20to%20continue%20its%20aggressive%20pursuit%20of%20crypto%20exchanges%20that%20violate%20trade%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20commissioner%20noted%20that%20there%20will%20be%20no%20tolerance%20for%20using%20VPNs%2C%20or%20any%20other%20actions%20that%20could%20circumvent%20KYC%20rules%2C%20including%20pop-up%20questions%20that%20merely%20ask%20users%20to%20attest%20that%20they%20aren't%20based%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20separate%20statement%2C%20CFTC%20Commissioner%20Caroline%20D.%20Pham%20said%20the%20CFTC's%20reach%20has%20no%20border.%20%26quot%3BIt%20should%20be%20crystal%20clear%20that%20the%20CFTC%20will%20not%20stop%20in%20its%20pursuit%20of%20non-U.S.%20entities%2C%26quot%3B%20Pham%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20swift%20action%20comes%20amidst%20a%20prolonged%20case%20set%20against%20FTX-founder%20SBF%2C%20who%20pleaded%20not%20guilty%20and%20was%20charged%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjury-sam-bankman-fried-guilty-seven-counts-fraud-manhattan-trial-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewith%20seven%20felony%20counts%2C%20including%20conspiracy%20to%20commit%20money%20laundering%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20remains%20at%20New%20York's%20Metropolitan%20Detention%20Center%20awaiting%20his%20sentencing%3Cs%3E.%3C%2Fs%3E%20He%20could%20face%20up%20to%20110%20years%20in%20prison.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcftc-aggressive-binance-case-is-a-warning-to-all-violators-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700778153000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655fbba99c7d23cb3b9f41cc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcftc-aggres